comments: VanVleet (TOR) commits a take foul on Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Portis (MIL) places his arms against Anunoby's (TOR) back and releases as he elevates for the rebound.
Siakam (TOR) reaches towards the ball and marginal contact occurs with Antetokounmpo (MIL).
Allen (MIL) reaches in and avoids initiating contact with Barnes (TOR) during his drive to the basket.
Barnes (TOR) moves laterally into Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and initiates body contact that affects Antetokounmpo's (MIL) SQBR during the drive.
Anunoby (TOR) and Lopez (MIL) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Lopez (MIL) moves underneath Anunoby (TOR) and dislodges him from his position.
Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is moving alongside Siakam's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Lopez (MIL) initiates body contact with Barnes (TOR) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
VanVleet (TOR) places his hands on Portis (MIL) as he releases the pass but the contact is marginal.
Lopez (MIL) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
VanVleet (TOR) initiates contact to Antetokounmpo's (MIL) right wrist that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Trent Jr. (TOR) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.

Antetokounmpo (MIL) initiates contact to VanVleet's (TOR) lower body that affects his ability to gather the loose ball. After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a common foul is confirmed.
Marginal body contact occurs as Siakam (TOR) defends Allen (MIL) during his drive in transition.
Trent Jr. (TOR) initiates contact to Allen's (MIL) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in Allen's (MIL) path and absorbs the contact.
Lopez (MIL) contests the shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Barnes's (TOR) arm after the release.
Milwaukee does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
VanVleet (TOR) and Portis (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Trent Jr. (TOR) and Beauchamp (MIL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
VanVleet (TOR) and Allen (MIL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, Allen (MIL) is assessed a flagrant foul-penalty (1) for delivering unnecessary contact to Trent Jr. (TOR) during his shot attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) establishes himself in Allen's (MIL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in Allen's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Lopez (MIL) places a hand on Barnes' (TOR) back during his driving shot attempt and the contact is marginal. Additionally, any contact after Barnes' release is marginal.
Trent Jr. (TOR) briefly places his arm to Allen's (MIL) front after gathering the entry pass and marginal body contact occurs defending his drive.
Allen (MIL) brings his off-arm toward Trent Jr. (TOR) and marginal contact occurs as Allen (MIL) releases away without applying any force.
Siakam (TOR) slightly extends his arm forward and marginal contact occurs to Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm after the release of his pass.
Siakam (TOR) initiates body contact with Portis (MIL) that affects his SQBR.

Barnes (TOR) establishes himself in Carter's (MIL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) is actively guarding Siakam (TOR) in the lane.
Lopez (MIL) legally contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Siakam (TOR) briefly places his arm against Carter's (MIL) front and slides his arm off as Carter (MIL) sets the screen.
Carter (MIL) establishes himself in Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

VanVleet (TOR) briefly places his hands on Lopez's (MIL) back before releasing during the rebound.
Lopez (MIL) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.

Lopez (MIL) briefly has a hand on the back of Barnes' (TOR) head during the rebound.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
